<div id="review_3579378964" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3579378964" />
    <a title="Crawford Voigt" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/109633859-crawford-voigt"><img alt="Crawford Voigt" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3579378964?book_show_action=true">Dec 24, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Crawford Voigt" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Crawford Voigt" href="/user/show/109633859-crawford-voigt">Crawford Voigt</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3579378964" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18098762959964479656">Prejean endures enormous emotional, spiritual, mental, and physical toll to enter into the lives of people on death row. That in itself is remarkable, but she doesn’t stop there - she also helps those on the other side of the issue by comforting and helping the families of the victims of murder. Prejean’s perspective and story are fascinating. This book also does a good job of shedding light on flagrant injustices in the American system of capital punishment. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

